# 1. 相棒と共に

Akito: Huff... Huff... Huff...
Akito: Phew...
Akito: (That's it for my run, but I still feel pretty good...)
Akito: (I think I'll do another lap after I get a drink of water. The vending machines should be...)
???: Ready, Max? Okay... Go get it!
???: Woof!
Akito: ...!
Akito: (That guy's here with his dog again. They've been here basically every day recently...)
Akito: (And that thing they're playing with... It's called a flying disc, right...?)
Owner: Hey, nice catch!
Max: Woof! Pant... Pant... Pant...!
Akito: (It's not that big a dog, but it looks pretty intense when it's running around...)
Akito: (Anyway, I need to grab some water.)
Owner: Alright, again! Catch—
Owner: Uh-oh. The wind...! Oh no!
Owner: Sir! I'm sorry, but our flying disc flew your way and...!
Akito: Hm?
Akito: (Their disc? Oh, here it is...)
Akito: Wait a second... If their disc's over here, then that means...
Max: Pant...! Pant...! Pant...!
Akito: No...! I-It's coming right towards me...!
Akito: ...!
Akito: (Geez, what do I do...?!)
Akito: (Wait, the disc...! If I throw it somewhere far in that direction...!)
Akito: Go! That way...!
Max: ...! Woof!
Akito: Th-There it goes...
Akito: (Did I go a little overboard there...? I'm not sure it'll be able to get...)
Max: W-Woof...!
Akito: What? No way... It caught it by jumping?
Owner: I-I'm so sorry...! Are you alright?!
Akito: Yes, I'm okay... I'm also sorry for throwing your disc without asking.
Owner: Oh, no! That's completely fine!
Owner: Still, seeing him charge towards you like that must've been very startling. I apologize for not being able to stop him sooner. I put an extra-long leash on him, but panicked and couldn't get a good grip on it...
Akito: (Oh, he did have a leash on. I got all worked up over noth—)
Max: Woof!
Akito: (Whoa!)
Owner: Welcome back, Max. That was an amazing catch you made back there! I didn't think you'd be able to get it after seeing how far our friend here threw your disc.
Akito: Haha...
Owner: Speaking of which, that was a beautiful throw! Your form was remarkable! Do you play ultimate a lot?
Akito: No, um... I haven't thrown a flying disc since I was little.
Owner: Really?! Then, you must be a natural athlete! I wish I could do what you can! I'm still working on how to throw one of these properly...
Akito: O-Oh, I see... That explains why you two have been here so often lately.
Owner: Huh? Haha. You saw?
Owner: I've actually been thinking about entering us into an agility contest that involves dogs catching discs... It's called “disc dog”.
Akito: An agility contest?
Owner: Yes! And those who do well in enough of them get to compete on the national stage.
Owner: Our dream is to become the number one team in the country!
Owner: Right, partner?!
Akito: (Partner...?)
Max: Woof!
Akito: Oh, I think he just replied to you...
Owner: Haha. I think so too... Sometimes it seems like he knows exactly what I'm saying.
Owner: But Border Collies are very smart, so maybe he does understand...
Akito: O-Oh, he's a Border Collie...?
Owner: Oh, I'm sorry. I've been going on and on about Max without introducing myself. My name is Itsuki Ishihara. And you are...?
Akito: Akito Shinonome. Also, I'm still in high school, so I'm not as old as you may think I am.
Ishihara: Wait, I'm also a high schooler! It's nice to meet you, Shinonome.
Akito: It was nice meeting you both. Anyway, I should get going...
Max: Pant... Pant... Pant...
Akito: (Huh?! H-He's looking right at me for some reason...)
Ishihara: What's the matter, Max? Oh, do you want Shinonome to pet you...?
Akito: Huh? He wants me to pet him?
Ishihara: Yes. After he's pulled off a nice play, he always sits like this and asks for pets.
Ishihara: He wants you to pet him because you were the one who threw the disc last.
Akito: (R-Really...?)
Max: Woof...
Akito: ...!
Ishihara: ...? Oh, wait...
Ishihara: Do you not like dogs, Shinonome?!
Akito: Umm, well... I'm not the biggest fan of them.
Ishihara: No, I'm so sorry for not asking sooner! Also, I apologize for keeping you here so long...!
Akito: Nah, that's okay. I should've said something sooner too.
Ishihara: Then, we'll be going!
Akito: Alright, see you around.
Akito: Phew...
Akito: (That guy was pretty rowdy...)
Akito: (But...)
Ishihara: Our dream is to become the number one team in the country!
Ishihara: Right, partner?!
Akito: (They're also working towards a goal as partners...)
Akito: Alright, I feel like running that extra mile now.
